             (the elder.)</p>
               <p>WILLIAM MAXFIELD. I am the prisoner's father, I am a <rs id="t18281204-254-viclabel1345" type="occupation">shoemaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281204-254-victim2191 t18281204-254-viclabel1345"></join>. On Tuesday, the 2d of December, I sent him into the yard to shake two pieces of carpet, he was gone a considerable time, and as I knew him to be rather bad, I looked out and saw the carpets there; I went down and saw a white cotton stocking in the corner; I then looked into my box, and missed a pair of trousers and a pair of braces which I had put there on the Monday; I went to the pawnbrokers' to tell them to stop them; I searched every where and could not find them; on the Wednesday he sent me the duplicate; these are the trousers.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281204-254-person2192">
                  JOHN 
                  GRIFFITHS
               <interp inst="t18281204-254-person2192" type="surname" value="GRIFFITHS"></interp>
